00:00:06.868 --> 00:00:10.355
16. 17. 18. 19. 20.

2
00:00:10.389 --> 00:00:12.702
Rest.

3
00:00:12.736 --> 00:00:14.221
Thanks.

4
00:00:14.255 --> 00:00:15.843
You watch.

5
00:00:15.877 --> 00:00:18.397
When I get
my new legs fitted.

6
00:00:18.432 --> 00:00:19.847
start doing laps
around this place.

7
00:00:19.881 --> 00:00:22.367
When you get your new legs
fitted. I'm taking you home.

8
00:00:22.401 --> 00:00:23.713
Did you get
my dress whites?

9
00:00:23.747 --> 00:00:25.163
I want to look sharp
for the fellas

10
00:00:25.197 --> 00:00:26.785
when I see them
on the Jamestomorrow.

11
00:00:26.819 --> 00:00:28.442
My first time back on board
since my...

12
00:00:28.476 --> 00:00:30.927
Eric.
The Jamesis gone.

13
00:00:30.961 --> 00:00:32.791
Mom and I went down to the pier
this morning

14
00:00:32.825 --> 00:00:35.276
to deliver USO packages
before I came here.

15
00:00:35.311 --> 00:00:37.692
and the ship isn't there.

16
00:00:37.727 --> 00:00:38.900
What?

17
00:00:38.935 --> 00:00:40.592
There were a bunch of other
family members down there.

18
00:00:40.626 --> 00:00:41.765
as surprised as we were.

19
00:00:41.800 --> 00:00:43.595
Please.
please don't be upset.

20
00:00:43.629 --> 00:00:46.046
I... I know you...
you had your... your heart set on going.

21
00:00:46.080 --> 00:00:47.978
and...

22
00:00:48.013 --> 00:00:50.257
Are you okay?

23
00:00:50.291 --> 00:00:51.637
It's on.

24
00:00:51.672 --> 00:00:54.261
The invasion...
this is it.

25
00:00:54.295 --> 00:00:55.641
D-Day's coming.

26
00:00:55.676 --> 00:00:58.299
The fact that we got out
without anyone knowing

27
00:00:58.334 --> 00:01:02.303
means we got a shot
to win this thing.

28
00:01:06.307 --> 00:01:08.137
Attention all hands.

29
00:01:08.171 --> 00:01:10.553
This is your captain.

30
00:01:10.587 --> 00:01:13.832
We have now crossed
south of the 18th parallel.

31
00:01:13.866 --> 00:01:15.592
In addition to
the Marines onboard.

32
00:01:15.627 --> 00:01:19.113
we have 300 more following us
on USSMichener.

33
00:01:19.148 --> 00:01:20.908
It's our job to see to it

34
00:01:20.942 --> 00:01:23.393
that they make it safely
to their destination.

35
00:01:23.428 --> 00:01:25.602
From this moment forward.
all contacts...

36
00:01:25.637 --> 00:01:28.398
surface. subsurface.
and airborne...

37
00:01:28.433 --> 00:01:29.917
are to be considered hostile.

38
00:01:29.951 --> 00:01:31.574
The battle before us

39
00:01:31.608 --> 00:01:33.921
will most likely
alter the course of the war.

40
00:01:33.955 --> 00:01:35.750
The conflict
that began in Mayport

41
00:01:35.785 --> 00:01:38.615
will end on the beaches
of South America.

42
00:01:38.650 --> 00:01:42.136
And we will be victorious.

43
00:01:42.171 --> 00:01:44.242
That is all.

