45
00:02:16.653 --> 00:02:18.345
Fresh intel from the rebels.

46
00:02:18.379 --> 00:02:19.898
There are now
two divisions of troops

47
00:02:19.932 --> 00:02:22.487
stationed in Panama
at the mouth of Gatun Locks.

48
00:02:22.521 --> 00:02:24.144
It's about 7.000 men.

49
00:02:24.178 --> 00:02:26.663
How? There's no way they rebuilt
the bridge at the Darien Gap.

50
00:02:26.698 --> 00:02:28.182
He must have pulled troops
off the front lines

51
00:02:28.217 --> 00:02:29.666
in Mexico and Nicaragua.

52
00:02:29.701 --> 00:02:32.290
The canal is Gustavo's center of
gravity. and he knows it.

53
00:02:32.324 --> 00:02:34.706
He's hunkering down.
waiting for us.

54
00:02:34.740 --> 00:02:36.156
In view of this intelligence.

55
00:02:36.190 --> 00:02:37.743
the planned-on landing
on the outskirts of

56
00:02:37.778 --> 00:02:39.814
Colon. Panama.
will not work.

57
00:02:39.849 --> 00:02:41.644
-So we pivot.
-Where?

58
00:02:41.678 --> 00:02:43.922
Where's a soft spot?
Where do we land? Costa Rica?

59
00:02:43.956 --> 00:02:45.889
Based on
Dr. Montano's war plans.

60
00:02:45.924 --> 00:02:47.995
Gustavo likes to hang back
until he's certain

61
00:02:48.029 --> 00:02:50.480
of where we're striking.
and then mount a counterattack.

62
00:02:50.515 --> 00:02:52.241
Yes. sir.
That's the Marines' experience.

63
00:02:52.275 --> 00:02:56.072
So any beach we choose will feel
like a soft spot at first.

64
00:02:56.106 --> 00:02:58.350
So we don't waste our energy
getting bogged down

65
00:02:58.385 --> 00:02:59.696
in a protracted
land engagement

66
00:02:59.731 --> 00:03:01.215
when we're outgunned
and outmanned.

67
00:03:01.250 --> 00:03:03.838
We go with the beach that leads
us straight to the king.

68
00:03:03.873 --> 00:03:07.014
What do we know of Gustavo's
defenses in Colombia?

69
00:03:07.048 --> 00:03:09.706
Armando's rebels reported
peculiar troop concentrations

70
00:03:09.741 --> 00:03:13.020
here. here.
and here.

71
00:03:13.054 --> 00:03:15.402
That's the area where Gustavo
was born.

72
00:03:15.436 --> 00:03:16.713
A town called Rubi.

73
00:03:16.748 --> 00:03:18.094
I bet he's there now.

74
00:03:18.128 --> 00:03:20.234
There are several options
for beaches to hit.

75
00:03:20.269 --> 00:03:22.616
The most obvious ones
here and here

76
00:03:22.650 --> 00:03:24.687
are most likely heavily mined
and protected.

77
00:03:24.721 --> 00:03:26.413
There is
a beach area here.

78
00:03:26.447 --> 00:03:27.862
Locals call it Playa Roja.

79
00:03:27.897 --> 00:03:29.933
Red Beach.
It's small.

80
00:03:29.968 --> 00:03:32.419
a little steep and rocky
for an amphibious landing.

81
00:03:32.453 --> 00:03:33.972
Which means it's probably
less guarded.

82
00:03:34.006 --> 00:03:37.113
So we'll make our landing there.
take out any troop bases.

83
00:03:37.147 --> 00:03:39.219
fight our way to Rubi.
and take out Tavo.

84
00:03:39.253 --> 00:03:43.257
Sir? Ma'am. we had eyes on our
Panama landing for weeks.

85
00:03:43.292 --> 00:03:45.570
We had every detail
of that place mapped out.

86
00:03:45.604 --> 00:03:48.711
No one's sending any Marines in
without a solid plan. Colonel.

87
00:03:48.745 --> 00:03:50.540
We'll send in a recon
and surveillance team

88
00:03:50.575 --> 00:03:52.577
to give us a complete picture
of the beach.

89
00:03:52.611 --> 00:03:54.717
If that checks out.
come morning.

90
00:03:54.751 --> 00:03:56.650
we're invading Colombia.

91
00:03:56.684 --> 00:03:58.755
Navy and Marines.
side by side.

92
00:04:00.309 --> 00:04:01.620
I'll brief the team. sir.

93
00:04:20.294 --> 00:04:21.744
Tavo.

94
00:04:21.778 --> 00:04:24.298
The Americans have been planning
an invasion from Cuba

95
00:04:24.333 --> 00:04:25.403
for months now.

96
00:04:25.437 --> 00:04:26.783
But now they know that

97
00:04:26.818 --> 00:04:28.854
they are not strong enough
to take Panama.

98
00:04:28.889 --> 00:04:32.755
They are going to look for
a place less strongly defended.

99
00:04:32.789 --> 00:04:35.033
We need to protect our base
in Colombia.

100
00:04:35.067 --> 00:04:37.311
-At the expense of the canal?
-Forget the canal.

101
00:04:37.346 --> 00:04:39.762
They cannot threaten the canal
with two or three ships.

102
00:04:39.796 --> 00:04:44.525
They are going to try to win
with a single strike.

103
00:04:57.849 --> 00:05:00.127
We do agree. Tavo.

104
00:05:00.161 --> 00:05:03.475
We all agree that
we are vulnerable.

105
00:05:03.510 --> 00:05:04.959
But it is up to you.

106
00:05:04.994 --> 00:05:08.894
Either we move our troops
back to Colombia.

107
00:05:08.929 --> 00:05:12.553
or we find someplace safe
to move you.

108
00:05:28.776 --> 00:05:31.192
Then what do you
want to do?

109
00:05:51.937 --> 00:05:54.043
900 miles
to the Colombian coast.

110
00:05:54.077 --> 00:05:55.838
I wonder how many shifts
Gustavo's got

111
00:05:55.872 --> 00:05:57.391
patrolling between
here and there.

112
00:05:57.426 --> 00:05:58.944
Two. maybe three.

113
00:05:58.979 --> 00:06:01.947
Losing that Mexican oil terminal
had to slow him down.

114
00:06:05.330 --> 00:06:06.435
What's wrong?

115
00:06:06.469 --> 00:06:08.678
That beach.

116
00:06:08.713 --> 00:06:12.026
We don't have any larger scale
charts of our landing zone?

117
00:06:36.188 --> 00:06:41.159
You... you look different
than the first time we met.

118
00:06:41.193 --> 00:06:44.162
You were haunted.

119
00:06:44.196 --> 00:06:45.646
Or maybe hunted.

120
00:06:45.681 --> 00:06:49.443
This is what
war has done to you.

121
00:07:05.701 --> 00:07:08.635
Cool movie projector.
Old-school.

122
00:07:08.669 --> 00:07:10.809
Yeah.
my old man sent it to me.

123
00:07:10.844 --> 00:07:13.467
He teaches film appreciation
at my old high school.

124
00:07:13.502 --> 00:07:15.469
Hi. Dad.
Hi. Cherry Hill.

125
00:07:15.504 --> 00:07:20.681
Dad wanted students to see films
as they were made.

126
00:07:20.716 --> 00:07:22.476
On film.

127
00:07:22.511 --> 00:07:24.098
So that's what
we're gonna do.

128
00:07:24.133 --> 00:07:25.755
We got a classic tonight.

129
00:07:25.790 --> 00:07:27.930
These guys are about to storm
the beaches of South America.

130
00:07:27.964 --> 00:07:30.380
A lot of them probably
won't come back alive.

131
00:07:30.415 --> 00:07:32.590
You think they're in the mood
for a movie?

132
00:07:32.624 --> 00:07:37.836
Well.
that's sort of the point.

133
00:07:40.011 --> 00:07:42.772
The way I see it.
I'm just lucky to be alive.

134
00:07:42.807 --> 00:07:45.534
The virus. famine.

135
00:07:45.568 --> 00:07:47.328
The war.

136
00:07:47.363 --> 00:07:50.608
Everybody I know is dead
except for these guys.

137
00:07:50.642 --> 00:07:52.057
You know what
I'm talking about?

138
00:07:52.092 --> 00:07:54.957
People are freaking out at home
right about now.

139
00:07:54.991 --> 00:07:56.199
Should they be?

140
00:07:56.234 --> 00:07:58.374
I don't know.
Maybe.

141
00:07:58.408 --> 00:08:00.859
I mean.
if we lose down here.

142
00:08:00.894 --> 00:08:03.724
there's not much to stop
the enemy from...

143
00:08:03.759 --> 00:08:05.174
I don't know.

144
00:08:05.208 --> 00:08:06.693
Moving in.

145
00:08:06.727 --> 00:08:08.522
So yeah. freaking out
sounds about right.

146
00:08:08.557 --> 00:08:10.835
You ever get afraid?

147
00:08:10.869 --> 00:08:13.423
Afraid. sure.

148
00:08:13.458 --> 00:08:16.047
Fear is something
you carry around

149
00:08:16.081 --> 00:08:18.843
with the rest of your gear.
You know. it's. uh...

150
00:08:18.877 --> 00:08:21.190
It's a lot like my boy Miller
used to say.

151
00:08:21.224 --> 00:08:22.812
You know. you. um...

152
00:08:22.847 --> 00:08:25.850
When you're on a mission
and your pack gets too heavy.

153
00:08:25.884 --> 00:08:27.437
you got to dump the stuff
that's useless.

154
00:08:27.472 --> 00:08:29.405
and fear is just
one of those things.

155
00:08:29.439 --> 00:08:31.718
Where's Miller now?

156
00:08:37.240 --> 00:08:39.070
Is this gonna
get broadcast?

157
00:08:39.104 --> 00:08:40.899
Yes. of course.

158
00:08:40.934 --> 00:08:43.730
What's up. Miller?

159
00:08:44.972 --> 00:08:49.598
Do your reps
and don't get lazy.

160
00:08:49.632 --> 00:08:52.393
I'ma see you stateside.

161
00:08:52.428 --> 00:08:55.949
And if you're out of shape.

162
00:08:55.983 --> 00:08:58.710
I'm gonna kick your ass.

163
00:09:13.449 --> 00:09:14.899
This man makes
battle decisions

164
00:09:14.933 --> 00:09:16.763
based on
seeing a bird in the sky.

165
00:09:16.797 --> 00:09:18.109
It's his wife.

166
00:09:18.143 --> 00:09:19.420
He executes loyal officers

167
00:09:19.455 --> 00:09:20.870
based on his fortune teller's
reading.

168
00:09:20.905 --> 00:09:23.459
Hector. how many of our troops
have to die for this...

169
00:09:23.493 --> 00:09:24.736
for this madman?

170
00:09:24.771 --> 00:09:27.601
Gentlemen. please.
have some respect.

171
00:09:27.636 --> 00:09:30.052
He brought us this far.
-You started this.

172
00:09:30.086 --> 00:09:31.605
And now you're afraid
to pull the trigger?

173
00:09:31.640 --> 00:09:32.917
What is your problem?!

174
00:09:32.951 --> 00:09:35.436
I have known this man
my whole life.

175
00:09:35.471 --> 00:09:36.748
We were kids together.

176
00:09:36.783 --> 00:09:39.440
The man you knew
is gone.

177
00:09:39.475 --> 00:09:41.788
General.
you know this is true.

178
00:09:41.822 --> 00:09:43.410
He is a danger
to us all now.

179
00:09:43.444 --> 00:09:44.894
Every hour we wait

180
00:09:44.929 --> 00:09:48.449
is another hour is puts our
entire continent at risk.

181
00:09:48.484 --> 00:09:50.141
I say we vote.

182
00:09:50.175 --> 00:09:52.419
Here and now.

183
00:09:57.976 --> 00:09:59.460
All right.

184
00:09:59.495 --> 00:10:01.773
Raise your hands
if you agree.

185
00:10:10.886 --> 00:10:14.959
At the Commanding Officer's
dinner.

186
00:10:14.993 --> 00:10:19.791
Gustavo Barros will die.

187
00:10:21.828 --> 00:10:24.106
Admiral.
I have something at SLQ-32.

188
00:10:24.140 --> 00:10:25.279
Bearing?

189
00:10:25.314 --> 00:10:27.005
0-1-5.

190
00:10:27.040 --> 00:10:28.489
Set general quarters.

191
00:10:28.524 --> 00:10:29.870
Aye. aye. sir.

192
00:10:29.905 --> 00:10:31.492
All hands
set general quarters.

193
00:10:31.527 --> 00:10:33.322
Micheneron semaphore
reports contact

194
00:10:33.356 --> 00:10:35.151
at 0-1-7
relative bearing.

195
00:10:35.186 --> 00:10:36.981
Gator. calculate range.

196
00:10:37.015 --> 00:10:38.672
Calculating.

197
00:10:38.707 --> 00:10:41.019
With current
bearing lines.

198
00:10:41.054 --> 00:10:43.125
I have them at 27 miles.

199
00:10:43.159 --> 00:10:44.678
Contact?

200
00:10:44.713 --> 00:10:47.681
Didn't expect he'd have ships
patrolling this far north.

201
00:10:47.716 --> 00:10:49.787
Maybe he has a fleet
bigger than we figured.

202
00:10:49.821 --> 00:10:52.790
I have two ships.
Noviembre-class corvettes.

203
00:10:52.824 --> 00:10:55.827
Doing a crossing pattern
up ahead. separating now.

204
00:10:55.862 --> 00:10:58.554
Sentries stalking the waters.
looking for us.

205
00:10:58.588 --> 00:11:01.212
Stop the ship.
All stop.

206
00:11:02.109 --> 00:11:05.009
Bridge. T.A.O. ...
Admiral's orders. all stop.

207
00:11:05.043 --> 00:11:07.736
All stop.
Zero turns. port and starboard.

208
00:11:11.222 --> 00:11:13.534
I can't see them.
They're still over the horizon.

209
00:11:13.569 --> 00:11:15.019
Gator.
any sign they heard us?

210
00:11:15.053 --> 00:11:17.331
No deviation from
established tracks as yet.

211
00:11:17.366 --> 00:11:19.368
Speeds are unchanged.

212
00:11:19.402 --> 00:11:21.611
Admiral's on the bridge.

213
00:11:21.646 --> 00:11:23.096
How the hell are we gonna
get past these guys?

214
00:11:23.130 --> 00:11:25.408
If it was just us. we might be
able to slip through.

215
00:11:25.443 --> 00:11:26.858
but with the Michener
behind us...

216
00:11:26.893 --> 00:11:29.827
It's like wearing a big
flashing sign. "We're here."

217
00:11:29.861 --> 00:11:31.207
We can't let them know
we're here.

218
00:11:31.242 --> 00:11:32.692
Even if we sink them.

219
00:11:32.726 --> 00:11:34.210
they'll radio back to Gustavo
that we're coming.

220
00:11:34.245 --> 00:11:35.867
The invasion's off.

221
00:11:35.902 --> 00:11:37.075
Ideas?

222
00:11:37.110 --> 00:11:39.112
Sirs. ma'am.

223
00:11:39.146 --> 00:11:40.838
If we calculate

224
00:11:40.872 --> 00:11:43.944
a moving plot of the area of
awareness of each ship.

225
00:11:43.979 --> 00:11:46.222
and we slip along
the edges of the two zones

226
00:11:46.257 --> 00:11:48.880
by starting and stopping.
veering sharply.

227
00:11:48.915 --> 00:11:50.951
and occasionally
going backwards.

228
00:11:50.986 --> 00:11:53.920
I think we can
just miss each one.

229
00:11:57.061 --> 00:11:59.477
It's like "Frogger."

230
00:12:00.581 --> 00:12:02.722
The old video game?

231
00:12:05.103 --> 00:12:06.795
All right. tell Michener
to tuck in behind us

232
00:12:06.829 --> 00:12:09.107
as close as they can.
Course?

233
00:12:09.142 --> 00:12:10.764
1-9-5.

234
00:12:10.799 --> 00:12:12.766
-O.O.D.. I have the conn.
-Aye. captain has the conn.

235
00:12:12.801 --> 00:12:14.595
-Helm. set course 1-9-5.
-Aye. ma'am.

236
00:12:14.630 --> 00:12:15.976
Setting course 1-9-5.

237
00:12:16.011 --> 00:12:18.668
Signalman. alert Michener
to come 200 yards astern.

238
00:12:18.703 --> 00:12:20.429
Aye. sir.

239
00:12:20.463 --> 00:12:22.707
We're gonna Frogger.

240
00:12:31.302 --> 00:12:34.581
First ship approaching CPA
in one minute.

241
00:12:34.615 --> 00:12:35.789
Slow her down.
Trail shafts.

242
00:12:35.824 --> 00:12:36.790
Aye. aye. ma'am.

243
00:12:41.174 --> 00:12:42.347
What's your current wind?

244
00:12:42.382 --> 00:12:44.798
Sir.
14 knots on the port beam.

245
00:12:44.833 --> 00:12:47.628
If we slow down any more.
we're gonna start to yaw.

246
00:12:47.663 --> 00:12:48.802
and then we'll be presenting

247
00:12:48.837 --> 00:12:50.459
a great big radar reflection
to them.

248
00:12:50.493 --> 00:12:51.978
Let her skid if the wind
starts to turn her.

249
00:12:52.012 --> 00:12:53.324
Aye. aye. sir.

250
00:12:53.358 --> 00:12:54.981
I've got a light on the horizon.
dead ahead.

251
00:12:55.015 --> 00:12:56.948
That's them.
but they're passing.

252
00:12:56.983 --> 00:13:01.988
They're passing CPA
in 10 seconds.

253
00:13:02.022 --> 00:13:05.785
Now seven. now five.

254
00:13:05.819 --> 00:13:07.476
Take your rudder
left 4 degrees.

255
00:13:07.510 --> 00:13:08.822
Aye. aye. ma'am.

256
00:13:08.857 --> 00:13:10.030
Rudder's left 4 degrees.

257
00:13:10.065 --> 00:13:12.032
Passing on my mark.

258
00:13:12.067 --> 00:13:13.723
Now!

259
00:13:13.758 --> 00:13:15.173
But here comes
the second one.

260
00:13:15.208 --> 00:13:16.657
Back one-third now!

261
00:13:16.692 --> 00:13:18.694
Signalman. tell Michener
to back off one-third.

262
00:13:18.728 --> 00:13:20.316
Yes. sir!

263
00:13:45.376 --> 00:13:47.136
That was way too close.

264
00:13:47.171 --> 00:13:51.727
Second vessel
is passing CPA...

265
00:13:51.761 --> 00:13:53.763
Now.

266
00:13:55.248 --> 00:13:56.559
All ahead full.

267
00:13:56.594 --> 00:13:58.665
Aye. aye. ma'am.
All ahead full.

268
00:14:02.013 --> 00:14:04.222
I think it worked.

269
00:14:04.257 --> 00:14:05.741
They didn't see us.

270
00:14:08.261 --> 00:14:09.849
Helm. come to course 2-6-5.

271
00:14:09.883 --> 00:14:11.712
Aye. ma'am.
Setting course 2-6-5.

272
00:14:11.747 --> 00:14:12.990
Nice job.

273
00:14:14.474 --> 00:14:18.098
I've thought it over. Hector.

274
00:14:18.133 --> 00:14:19.997
And I've made
my decision.

275
00:14:20.031 --> 00:14:24.587
We're going to move a battalion
of troops back to Colombia.

276
00:14:24.622 --> 00:14:26.417
Conchita
showed me the signs.

277
00:14:26.451 --> 00:14:28.729
and they're auspicious
for moving in this direction.

278
00:14:28.764 --> 00:14:31.940
Please send my thanks
to your oracle.

279
00:14:49.060 --> 00:14:51.028
Thank you.

280
00:14:51.062 --> 00:14:53.478
For everything.

281
00:14:53.513 --> 00:14:55.446
Of course.

282
00:14:55.480 --> 00:14:57.448
Always.

283
00:15:09.529 --> 00:15:11.565
Sorry. ma'am.
this is off-limits.

284
00:15:11.600 --> 00:15:13.498
No cameras.

285
00:15:17.709 --> 00:15:19.677
Unlike our initial
target in Panama.

286
00:15:19.711 --> 00:15:22.956
this beach hasn't been
mapped closely.

287
00:15:22.991 --> 00:15:25.096
And it's right in
Gustavo's backyard.

288
00:15:25.131 --> 00:15:28.306
I want intel on the surf.
the sand. and the landing area.

289
00:15:28.341 --> 00:15:33.587
We need to know if and where the
enemy has placed guns or troops.

290
00:15:33.622 --> 00:15:35.762
A few hundred souls
will be storming that beach

291
00:15:35.796 --> 00:15:37.315
tomorrow before dawn.

292
00:15:37.350 --> 00:15:38.938
I don't want any surprises.

293
00:15:38.972 --> 00:15:40.836
- Are we clear?
- Yes. sir!

294
00:15:40.870 --> 00:15:43.632
Green. Burk. Wolf. you'll be
headed back to the ship tonight.

295
00:15:43.666 --> 00:15:46.152
Good luck
and see you in a few hours.

296
00:15:46.186 --> 00:15:48.982
Kandie. Barco. you're staying
ashore to set targets.

297
00:15:49.017 --> 00:15:50.639
Stay safe. stay quiet.

298
00:15:52.020 --> 00:15:53.366
See you at dawn.

299
00:16:01.132 --> 00:16:02.996
Got your swim legs?

300
00:16:03.031 --> 00:16:05.619
You know I do.

301
00:16:05.654 --> 00:16:08.553
What is it?

302
00:16:08.588 --> 00:16:11.108
This is my last mission.

303
00:16:11.142 --> 00:16:14.007
I mean it.

304
00:16:14.042 --> 00:16:15.388
After this.

305
00:16:15.422 --> 00:16:18.632
after we do
what we came here to do.

306
00:16:18.667 --> 00:16:20.703
I'm out.
I'm done with war.

307
00:16:20.738 --> 00:16:22.291
And if after all this.

308
00:16:22.326 --> 00:16:25.536
you and Frankie can stand being
around whatever's left of me.

309
00:16:25.570 --> 00:16:28.711
I'd love to come home.

310
00:16:30.610 --> 00:16:32.474
You mean that?

311
00:16:32.508 --> 00:16:35.891
What do you say.
Captain?

312
00:16:38.928 --> 00:16:41.897
We'll talk about it
when you come back.

313
00:16:41.931 --> 00:16:44.589
Okay.

314
00:16:44.624 --> 00:16:48.214
You just make damn sure
you come back.

315
00:16:59.777 --> 00:17:02.055
Gear up. rookie.

316
00:17:02.090 --> 00:17:04.920
We're out of here.

317
00:17:10.098 --> 00:17:10.960
Bird is away.

318
00:17:10.995 --> 00:17:12.169
Can we reach them
on one watt?

319
00:17:12.203 --> 00:17:14.033
Yes. sir!
For another minute or two.

320
00:17:14.067 --> 00:17:17.415
Brawler. this is Nathan James.
You got your radio on?

321
00:17:17.450 --> 00:17:21.074
Nathan James.we are currently
six miles from target.

322
00:17:21.109 --> 00:17:22.765
Horizon's clear.

323
00:17:22.800 --> 00:17:25.251
Try to keep that bird in
one piece till you get back.

324
00:17:25.285 --> 00:17:27.184
Copy that. sir.

325
00:17:27.218 --> 00:17:29.186
Unless you see something
that threatens the mission.

326
00:17:29.220 --> 00:17:30.463
go radio silent now.

327
00:17:30.497 --> 00:17:32.603
Godspeed.
Nathan Jamesout.

328
00:17:32.637 --> 00:17:34.708
Going zip lip now. sir.

329
00:17:34.743 --> 00:17:36.538
Catch you on the flip side.

330
00:17:36.572 --> 00:17:37.953
T.A.O..
mark the time.

331
00:17:37.987 --> 00:17:39.955
Recon team will drop
in three minutes.

332
00:17:56.834 --> 00:17:58.560
Drop zone in 10 seconds!

333
00:17:58.594 --> 00:18:00.665
Gonna have a 15-foot jump.

334
00:18:14.852 --> 00:18:18.304
My grandfather piloted
a landing craft into Normandy.

335
00:18:18.338 --> 00:18:20.685
A year later. he joined
the 7th Fleet in the Pacific.

336
00:18:20.720 --> 00:18:23.654
And here we are.
doing it all over again.

337
00:18:23.688 --> 00:18:26.277
History tends to repeat.

338
00:18:26.312 --> 00:18:29.280
A lesson you can share with your
class next semester. professor.

339
00:18:59.207 --> 00:19:01.174
They should be
on the beach by now.

340
00:19:09.044 --> 00:19:12.496
This is Cobra One.
commencing periphery scout.

341
00:19:12.530 --> 00:19:17.190
Cobra Two and Four.
establishing hide site.

342
00:19:17.225 --> 00:19:22.161
Cobra Three and Five
commencing hydrographic survey.

343
00:20:06.412 --> 00:20:08.724
That's right. boys.

344
00:20:08.759 --> 00:20:12.072
Just another
night at the beach.

345
00:20:18.665 --> 00:20:20.598
Cobra Team.
this is Cobra Five.

346
00:20:20.633 --> 00:20:22.255
Well. the good news is.
so far.

347
00:20:22.290 --> 00:20:24.982
everything is consistent with
what we've expected to find.

348
00:20:25.016 --> 00:20:26.949
Copy that. Cobra Five.

349
00:20:26.984 --> 00:20:28.641
And the bad news?

350
00:20:28.675 --> 00:20:30.574
Well. so far.
everything is consistent

351
00:20:30.608 --> 00:20:32.265
with what we expected to find.

352
00:20:32.300 --> 00:20:33.439
We have steep inclines

353
00:20:33.473 --> 00:20:34.992
and various near-surface
obstructions.

354
00:20:35.026 --> 00:20:37.374
I'm gonna suggest the Admiral
rename this operation

355
00:20:37.408 --> 00:20:38.616
"Less Than Ideal."

356
00:20:38.651 --> 00:20:40.239
This is Cobra One.

357
00:20:40.273 --> 00:20:43.966
I've got two observation posts
with machine-gun placements.

358
00:20:44.001 --> 00:20:45.451
Looks like .240s.

359
00:20:45.485 --> 00:20:47.315
250 meters apart.

360
00:20:47.349 --> 00:20:50.766
33 and 36 yards
from shore.

361
00:20:50.801 --> 00:20:54.598
A dozen or so military-aged
males standing watch.

362
00:20:54.632 --> 00:20:58.602
Some kind of makeshift barracks
on the bluff.

363
00:20:58.636 --> 00:21:00.604
Hard to tell how many more
could be up there.

364
00:21:00.638 --> 00:21:02.985
Copy that. Cobra One.

365
00:21:03.779 --> 00:21:06.126
Ready?
-Ready!

366
00:21:10.130 --> 00:21:12.857
Cobra Two. antenna is set.

367
00:21:12.892 --> 00:21:15.515
Establishing connection
with Navy Spear.

368
00:21:18.000 --> 00:21:20.796
I count swell periods of
five to seven seconds.

369
00:21:20.831 --> 00:21:23.178
Direction is north. northwest.

370
00:21:23.212 --> 00:21:25.353
It's gonna be a bumpy climb
up the beach.

371
00:21:25.387 --> 00:21:28.010
I got the pucks.

372
00:21:31.497 --> 00:21:33.809
XO. you all right?

373
00:21:34.914 --> 00:21:37.330
It's so beautiful here.
man.

374
00:21:37.365 --> 00:21:39.332
It's peaceful.

375
00:21:39.367 --> 00:21:41.127
It's hard to believe
how different

376
00:21:41.161 --> 00:21:44.510
this place is gonna be
in a few hours.

377
00:21:45.925 --> 00:21:47.858
Let's go.

378
00:21:53.035 --> 00:21:55.244
Navy Spear.
this is Cobra Four.

379
00:21:55.279 --> 00:21:56.729
Drinks are on the house.
Over.

380
00:21:56.763 --> 00:21:58.455
Cobra Four.
this is Stonewall Six.

381
00:21:58.489 --> 00:21:59.835
Go ahead with sit rep.

382
00:21:59.870 --> 00:22:02.010
Two anti-air
artillery pieces.

383
00:22:02.044 --> 00:22:04.495
Half a dozen men
with AK-47s.

384
00:22:04.530 --> 00:22:06.842
Change of command TBD.

385
00:22:06.877 --> 00:22:09.224
Regular patrol
every 15 minutes.

386
00:22:09.258 --> 00:22:12.676
Conbeachrep consistent with
previous satellite imagery.

387
00:22:12.710 --> 00:22:14.402
Coral outcroppings
and obstructions

388
00:22:14.436 --> 00:22:17.025
currently being marked in
the water with infrared pucks.

389
00:22:17.059 --> 00:22:19.234
Cans.

390
00:22:23.583 --> 00:22:24.929
Hear that?

391
00:22:24.964 --> 00:22:26.034
Marking.

392
00:22:28.623 --> 00:22:31.488
I'm sorry. sir.
I'm not hearing anything.

393
00:22:31.522 --> 00:22:33.869
A vessel. sir?
-The battleship.

394
00:22:33.904 --> 00:22:35.906
No sign of her
since the spring.

395
00:22:35.940 --> 00:22:37.632
She's back.

396
00:22:41.567 --> 00:22:43.914
Enhancing
low frequencies.

397
00:22:45.087 --> 00:22:47.366
Maybe they cut their engines.
sir.

398
00:22:57.445 --> 00:23:00.448
Admiral. surface contact
on passive bearing 0-4-4.

399
00:23:00.482 --> 00:23:02.104
Now 0-4-3.

400
00:23:02.139 --> 00:23:04.900
Unable to identify on SLQ-32.
-There is a ship out there.

401
00:23:04.935 --> 00:23:06.695
Damn. it's right between us
and our team on the beach.

402
00:23:06.730 --> 00:23:08.214
-Sonar?
-I have it.

403
00:23:08.248 --> 00:23:09.940
Scanning profiles now.

404
00:23:11.631 --> 00:23:12.874
It's a corvette.

405
00:23:12.908 --> 00:23:14.289
They followed us south?

406
00:23:14.323 --> 00:23:16.464
No. sir. Previous contacts
were Noviembres.

407
00:23:16.498 --> 00:23:18.466
This...
this is an Esporaclass.

408
00:23:18.500 --> 00:23:20.088
Another ship.

409
00:23:20.122 --> 00:23:21.986
This far east of Panama?

410
00:23:24.955 --> 00:23:26.922
There's no sign they've changed
course or speed.

411
00:23:26.957 --> 00:23:28.096
I don't think
they've seen us yet.

412
00:23:28.130 --> 00:23:29.891
Even if we stay
at Emcon Alpha.

413
00:23:29.925 --> 00:23:31.444
chances are she'll find us
or Michenervery soon.

414
00:23:31.479 --> 00:23:34.413
We move. we're found out.
and the operation is blown.

415
00:23:34.447 --> 00:23:35.759
We stay put. same outcome.

416
00:23:35.793 --> 00:23:37.968
And Cobra team is stranded
on the beach.

417
00:23:38.002 --> 00:23:40.315
We have to be
ready to fight.

418
00:23:40.349 --> 00:23:42.593
CIC. bridge.

419
00:23:42.628 --> 00:23:44.906
Enable all manual bypass
settings for weapons.

420
00:23:44.940 --> 00:23:47.460
T.A.O.. aye.
dispatching now.

421
00:23:47.495 --> 00:23:49.289
Don't energize
until my command.

422
00:23:49.324 --> 00:23:51.119
Worse comes to worst.

423
00:23:51.153 --> 00:23:52.948
we're gonna have to sacrifice
Nathan Jamesto save Michener.

424
00:23:52.983 --> 00:23:54.571
Keep those Marines
on mission.

425
00:23:54.605 --> 00:23:56.987
By that time. Gustavo's entire
army will be at the beach.

426
00:23:57.021 --> 00:23:59.299
There won't be
any mission.

427
00:23:59.334 --> 00:24:00.473
Uh. ma'am?

428
00:24:00.508 --> 00:24:01.509
Sirs?

429
00:24:01.543 --> 00:24:03.165
If I may?

430
00:24:03.200 --> 00:24:04.960
I think I know a way
for us to stay invisible.

431
00:24:04.995 --> 00:24:06.272
Jamming?
They'll sense that.

432
00:24:06.306 --> 00:24:07.653
Sir. I can do it
without them even knowing

433
00:24:07.687 --> 00:24:09.033
that their system's
being jammed.

434
00:24:09.068 --> 00:24:11.484
-How?
-Send out the helo.

435
00:24:11.519 --> 00:24:14.970
align it with their bow. and
emit a custom-coded HF signal.

436
00:24:15.005 --> 00:24:17.386
Now. the software doesn't
kill the radar entirely.

437
00:24:17.421 --> 00:24:20.631
but it creates a loop.
giving them false imagery.

438
00:24:20.666 --> 00:24:22.771
Software?
I never heard of it.

439
00:24:22.806 --> 00:24:25.015
Uh. it's new. sir.

440
00:24:25.049 --> 00:24:27.155
And full disclosure.
untested.

441
00:24:27.189 --> 00:24:29.640
I started developing it
in my JMO course

442
00:24:29.675 --> 00:24:30.848
before we got called up.

443
00:24:30.883 --> 00:24:32.540
Kind of a pet project.

444
00:24:32.574 --> 00:24:33.782
Show us.

445
00:24:33.817 --> 00:24:35.370
Mother.
this is Brawler.

446
00:24:35.404 --> 00:24:36.509
Radar jammer on board.

447
00:24:36.544 --> 00:24:37.821
We are ready for action.

448
00:24:37.855 --> 00:24:39.201
Copy that. Brawler.

449
00:24:39.236 --> 00:24:42.515
So. once the HF signal's
picked up on enemy radar.

450
00:24:42.550 --> 00:24:44.344
they won't be able to see us.

451
00:24:44.379 --> 00:24:46.174
even though our helo's
right in front of them?

452
00:24:46.208 --> 00:24:48.866
Yes. sir. I've only been able to
test this on commercial radar.

453
00:24:48.901 --> 00:24:51.524
but it was designed to operate
above 1.000 megahertz.

454
00:24:51.559 --> 00:24:53.353
It'll render. sir.

455
00:24:53.388 --> 00:24:55.079
I know it.

456
00:24:55.114 --> 00:24:56.218
We good?

457
00:24:56.253 --> 00:24:58.669
Going in low. slow.
and without a glow.

458
00:24:58.704 --> 00:25:00.533
Let's hope this nerd
knows what he's doing.

459
00:25:00.568 --> 00:25:01.983
Here we go. girls!

460
00:25:02.017 --> 00:25:05.055
Mother.
we are seven mikes to target.

461
00:25:05.089 --> 00:25:06.815
The entire war effort
is riding on

462
00:25:06.850 --> 00:25:08.921
an untested
invisibility cloak.

463
00:25:08.955 --> 00:25:12.027
This programmer
hasn't failed us yet.

464
00:25:23.763 --> 00:25:26.697
The corvette's still in its
standard search pattern. ma'am.

465
00:25:26.732 --> 00:25:29.528
Good. Let's hope
we can keep it that way.

466
00:25:32.392 --> 00:25:35.223
Helo should be coming up on
corvette's radar range soon.

467
00:25:35.257 --> 00:25:36.431
Brawler. Mother.

468
00:25:36.465 --> 00:25:38.019
Initiate jamming sequence.

469
00:25:44.473 --> 00:25:46.752
Uh. Ensign?

470
00:25:46.786 --> 00:25:50.583
Shouldn't this thing be
whooshing or something?

471
00:25:50.618 --> 00:25:51.757
Negative. ma'am.

472
00:25:51.791 --> 00:25:53.482
Don't worry. It's engaged.

473
00:25:58.142 --> 00:26:00.386
I marked three areas
of obstruction.

474
00:26:00.420 --> 00:26:03.320
IR signals are set to turn on
just before we launch.

475
00:26:03.354 --> 00:26:05.287
We got about
a dozen pucks left.

476
00:26:05.322 --> 00:26:08.049
Let's carve out a lane
for the tracks.

477
00:26:30.658 --> 00:26:33.626
Mother. this is Brawler.
We are in position.

478
00:26:46.121 --> 00:26:48.641
Here she comes.

479
00:26:53.404 --> 00:26:57.167
And we're live.
Mother.

480
00:27:01.240 --> 00:27:03.760
Corvette should be
panning the helo as we speak.

481
00:27:03.794 --> 00:27:04.761
Is it working?

482
00:27:04.795 --> 00:27:07.177
Yes. sir. Admiral.
It should be.

483
00:27:07.211 --> 00:27:09.524
Monitoring the corvette's
HF chatter now.

484
00:27:09.558 --> 00:27:12.838
They're silent.
No alerts. no alarms.

485
00:27:19.189 --> 00:27:20.811
We're drowning in radar
right now.

486
00:27:20.846 --> 00:27:23.158
I can't believe
they can't see us.

487
00:27:26.852 --> 00:27:29.061
I got something!

488
00:27:38.380 --> 00:27:39.865
Biologicals.

489
00:27:39.899 --> 00:27:42.661
Dolphins.

490
00:27:49.460 --> 00:27:51.221
Corvette
is changing course.

491
00:27:51.255 --> 00:27:52.981
Toward Nathan James.

492
00:27:53.016 --> 00:27:54.845
Prepare to drop
Emcon Alpha!

493
00:27:56.433 --> 00:27:58.090
Hold on.

494
00:27:58.124 --> 00:27:59.608
They're talking.

495
00:27:59.643 --> 00:28:03.405
Gran Colombia Reina.
reporting in.

496
00:28:03.440 --> 00:28:06.650
Minor adjustment
to avoid marine interference.

497
00:28:07.755 --> 00:28:09.688
Resuming
the search pattern.

498
00:28:12.104 --> 00:28:14.900
Nathan Jamesis now
clear of enemy ship.

499
00:28:14.934 --> 00:28:16.729
The jamming worked.

500
00:28:16.764 --> 00:28:20.629
Sir?
If you don't mind my saying.

501
00:28:20.664 --> 00:28:24.254
you sailors sure know how
to put on a show.

502
00:28:24.288 --> 00:28:27.740
Just another day at sea.
Colonel.

503
00:28:43.791 --> 00:28:46.621
Shit.

504
00:28:46.655 --> 00:28:50.038
Cobra Team. we have a contact.

505
00:29:36.878 --> 00:29:38.190
Should we engage?

506
00:29:38.224 --> 00:29:39.778
Negative.

507
00:29:39.812 --> 00:29:41.331
We can't
give up our position.

508
00:29:41.365 --> 00:29:42.988
They can handle it.

509
00:29:49.028 --> 00:29:51.306
Come on. boys.

510
00:30:07.150 --> 00:30:08.496
Oh. no.

511
00:30:08.530 --> 00:30:10.187
They found the marker!

512
00:30:28.757 --> 00:30:30.829
Fernando.

513
00:30:34.073 --> 00:30:36.282
Fernando?

514
00:30:46.706 --> 00:30:49.019
You take the forepeak.
I'll clear below aft.

515
00:31:24.917 --> 00:31:26.919
Okay. Burk!

516
00:31:26.954 --> 00:31:29.232
You okay?

517
00:31:29.266 --> 00:31:32.028
Come on. man.
You got to get up.

518
00:31:33.305 --> 00:31:34.893
Come on.

519
00:31:37.240 --> 00:31:39.932
Come on. I got you.

520
00:31:44.178 --> 00:31:45.938
God damn. Danny.

521
00:31:45.973 --> 00:31:48.941
Oh. God damn.

522
00:31:51.254 --> 00:31:52.634
Come on. Burk.

523
00:31:52.669 --> 00:31:54.982
Hey. stay with me now.

524
00:31:55.016 --> 00:31:56.086
Burk.

525
00:32:26.289 --> 00:32:28.153
Burk.

526
00:32:52.039 --> 00:32:53.799
Hector! Brother!

527
00:32:53.833 --> 00:32:55.318
Welcome.

528
00:32:55.352 --> 00:32:56.905
Come in.

529
00:32:56.940 --> 00:32:59.322
Felipe already started.
He's hungry.

530
00:32:59.356 --> 00:33:01.807
But we can eat now.

531
00:33:01.841 --> 00:33:03.740
Sit.

532
00:33:08.745 --> 00:33:11.748
The generals. unfortunately.
won't be joining us.

533
00:33:15.096 --> 00:33:19.031
Sí.Tavo.

534
00:33:19.066 --> 00:33:21.620
Tavo.
what is going on?

535
00:33:23.104 --> 00:33:24.899
Bad news. Hector.

536
00:33:24.933 --> 00:33:26.935
The generals?

537
00:33:26.970 --> 00:33:28.834
They were plotting
against me.

538
00:33:28.868 --> 00:33:31.009
Who. Tavo?

539
00:33:31.043 --> 00:33:32.493
Eat. Hector.

540
00:33:32.527 --> 00:33:35.047
Gazpacho shouldn't be allowed
to warm to room temperature.

541
00:33:35.082 --> 00:33:36.359
It's good.

542
00:33:38.706 --> 00:33:40.328
There must be a mistake.

543
00:33:40.363 --> 00:33:44.056
You're telling me there was
a coup amongst my generals?

544
00:33:44.091 --> 00:33:45.506
Your generals?

545
00:33:45.540 --> 00:33:48.371
I hope they aren't
your generals. Hector.

546
00:33:48.405 --> 00:33:49.717
No.

547
00:33:49.751 --> 00:33:50.925
They're cowards.

548
00:33:50.959 --> 00:33:52.478
And I warned you
against them.

549
00:33:58.139 --> 00:34:00.107
Are you sure?

550
00:34:00.141 --> 00:34:03.041
I've known these men
a very long time.

551
00:34:03.075 --> 00:34:04.870
I would have
heard something.

552
00:34:04.904 --> 00:34:06.734
There is no mistake.
Hector.

553
00:34:06.768 --> 00:34:09.150
So you have proof?

554
00:34:11.083 --> 00:34:12.636
Conchita saw it.

555
00:34:12.671 --> 00:34:15.156
In the cards.

556
00:34:29.481 --> 00:34:31.483
Tavo.

557
00:34:39.594 --> 00:34:41.562
We cannot play
with men's lives.

558
00:34:41.596 --> 00:34:43.771
These cards cannot
always be trusted.

559
00:34:43.805 --> 00:34:45.704
They confessed.

560
00:34:47.947 --> 00:34:52.469
Chacon. Bianchi. Rodriguez.
Munos. Moreno.

561
00:34:52.504 --> 00:34:54.782
Every single one of them.

562
00:34:54.816 --> 00:34:57.509
Oh. my God.

563
00:34:57.543 --> 00:35:00.822
But it doesn't matter.
not really.

564
00:35:00.857 --> 00:35:02.859
All I wanted to know...
the only thing I asked them

565
00:35:02.893 --> 00:35:05.620
before I removed
their intestines was.

566
00:35:05.655 --> 00:35:08.347
did Hector know?

567
00:35:11.385 --> 00:35:14.767
Of course.
none of them gave you up.

568
00:35:14.802 --> 00:35:17.149
But they gave each other up
real quick.

569
00:35:17.184 --> 00:35:20.118
But you?

570
00:35:21.567 --> 00:35:23.362
Not you.

571
00:35:23.397 --> 00:35:25.847
Then
I started feeling bad.

572
00:35:27.194 --> 00:35:29.299
For doubting you.

573
00:35:29.334 --> 00:35:31.715
It's... it's okay.

574
00:35:31.750 --> 00:35:32.889
No. no. no. no.

575
00:35:32.923 --> 00:35:35.719
With all the pressure
from the war. I've...

576
00:35:35.754 --> 00:35:39.344
I know
I've gone a little crazy.

577
00:35:39.378 --> 00:35:41.069
And I'm sorry
about that.

578
00:35:41.104 --> 00:35:43.382
You don't have to apologize.
Tavo.

579
00:35:43.417 --> 00:35:46.213
I support you.
Always.

580
00:35:46.247 --> 00:35:48.629
Of course you do.
Of course. I know.

581
00:35:48.663 --> 00:35:51.701
That is why I want you
to lead the investigation

582
00:35:51.735 --> 00:35:54.082
to see just how far down
this conspiracy goes.

583
00:35:54.117 --> 00:35:56.188
I want it torn out
by the roots!

584
00:35:56.223 --> 00:35:59.087
Sí.Tavo.

585
00:35:59.122 --> 00:36:01.193
I will handle it
personally.

586
00:36:01.228 --> 00:36:03.161
Like always.

587
00:36:04.610 --> 00:36:06.440
Like always.

588
00:36:10.271 --> 00:36:12.204
Conchita.

589
00:36:40.819 --> 00:36:44.892
Hector. my friend.

590
00:36:44.926 --> 00:36:47.032
My brother.

591
00:36:51.830 --> 00:36:53.970
If you're gonna stab a man
in the back.

592
00:36:54.004 --> 00:36:57.318
the least that you can do
is look him in the eye!

593
00:37:02.116 --> 00:37:03.980
Tavo.

594
00:37:08.847 --> 00:37:10.297
Dios...

595
00:37:21.342 --> 00:37:23.758
VivaTavo.

596
00:37:59.863 --> 00:38:02.521
You can wear your uniform home.
but not longer than 30 days.

597
00:38:02.556 --> 00:38:06.042
- Suppose they paid you off in South Africa.
- And you went home on foot.

598
00:38:06.076 --> 00:38:07.699
They can't tell you
how to go home.

599
00:38:07.733 --> 00:38:09.045
You can go home
on a pogo stick.

600
00:38:09.079 --> 00:38:10.633
You got to
think of your mother.

601
00:38:10.667 --> 00:38:12.324
The regulations
clearly state...

602
00:38:12.359 --> 00:38:13.705
That only applies
to Marines.

603
00:38:13.739 --> 00:38:15.500
You ain't really
a Marine anymore.

604
00:38:15.534 --> 00:38:17.295
Besides. the regulations
is very elastic.

605
00:38:17.329 --> 00:38:19.504
I was even a colonel once
for a couple of days.

606
00:38:19.538 --> 00:38:21.368
And a brig hound
for a couple of months.

607
00:38:22.817 --> 00:38:24.957
Back it up 20 seconds.
please.

608
00:38:24.992 --> 00:38:27.546
14:22.

609
00:38:32.896 --> 00:38:35.071
You're sure
that's the correct marker?

610
00:38:35.105 --> 00:38:36.486
Admiral Chandler says

611
00:38:36.521 --> 00:38:38.246
he heard the battleship
between these frames?

612
00:38:38.281 --> 00:38:39.627
I'm positive. ma'am.

613
00:38:39.662 --> 00:38:41.491
I've studied the recording
from end to end.

614
00:38:41.526 --> 00:38:44.080
and I can't find anything.

615
00:38:52.053 --> 00:38:54.711
Guess Gator's got
the right idea.

616
00:38:54.746 --> 00:38:56.334
Try and keep their minds
off things.

617
00:38:56.368 --> 00:38:58.888
even just for a few hours.

618
00:38:58.922 --> 00:39:01.546
So. tell me. Admiral.

619
00:39:01.580 --> 00:39:05.066
What's going through your head
on the night before D-Day?

620
00:39:07.068 --> 00:39:08.518
Nathan James.

621
00:39:08.553 --> 00:39:10.278
The ship?

622
00:39:10.313 --> 00:39:13.765
The sailor.
Ship's namesake.

623
00:39:13.799 --> 00:39:17.838
Captain Nathan James
skippered a PT boat

624
00:39:17.872 --> 00:39:20.012
during the war
in the Pacific.

625
00:39:20.047 --> 00:39:22.774
His fleet was decimated.

626
00:39:22.808 --> 00:39:25.224
His boat was all
that was left standing

627
00:39:25.259 --> 00:39:27.434
against nine
Japanese destroyers.

628
00:39:27.468 --> 00:39:30.575
The boat sank beneath him.

629
00:39:30.609 --> 00:39:35.200
Not before he stopped
the enemy's advance.

630
00:39:35.234 --> 00:39:37.064
He single-handedly saved

631
00:39:37.098 --> 00:39:39.791
a fleet of newly repaired
American destroyers

632
00:39:39.825 --> 00:39:41.931
coming out of Pearl Harbor

633
00:39:41.965 --> 00:39:45.452
carrying thousands of sailors
into the fight.

634
00:39:45.486 --> 00:39:50.595
Captain James said.
"War is a beast.

635
00:39:50.629 --> 00:39:53.632
It appears in many forms.

636
00:39:53.667 --> 00:39:57.291
Sometimes it's the beast
you face head on.

637
00:39:57.325 --> 00:40:02.158
out on
the field of battle.

638
00:40:02.192 --> 00:40:03.918
As equals.

639
00:40:03.953 --> 00:40:06.300
Sometimes
the beast hides out.

640
00:40:06.334 --> 00:40:11.443
Lurking somewhere in the deep.
biding its time

641
00:40:11.478 --> 00:40:17.035
until. when your guard is
dropped. it comes for you."

642
00:40:18.519 --> 00:40:21.419
"Bloodthirsty and merciless."

643
00:40:25.595 --> 00:40:27.804
"And it drags you under.

644
00:40:27.839 --> 00:40:32.706
On any given day. you never know
which beast you're gonna face."

645
00:40:34.673 --> 00:40:36.675
Which beast is it for you.
Admiral?

646
00:40:36.710 --> 00:40:38.746
All aboard!

647
00:40:38.781 --> 00:40:40.955
I knew the Marines
could do almost anything.

648
00:40:40.990 --> 00:40:43.510
but I never knew they could do
anything like this.

649
00:40:43.544 --> 00:40:45.028
You've got no idea.

649
00:40:46.305 --> 00:41:46.619
